  "description": "This week&#8217;s episode is with CWO Grant Lawson.  Grant has served as a crewman in the Royal Canadian Armoured Corps in two Regiments: the Ontario Regiment and the Queen&#8217;s York Rangers.  He has deployed to the Middle East, the former Yugoslavia and most recently to Afghanistan. His current appointment takes him out of his usual arcs and into the Infantry, serving as the Regimental Sergeant-Major of the Royal Hamilton Light Infantry.  Grant is a good friend and a trusted advisor.  [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>This week&#8217;s episode is with CWO Grant Lawson.  Grant has served as a crewman in the <a title=\"The Royal Canadian Armoured Corps Association\" href=\"http://www.rcaca.org/En/indexLM.asp?ID=1\" target=\"_blank\">Royal Canadian Armoured Corps</a> in two Regiments: the <a title=\"The Ontario Regiment Museum\" href=\"http://www.ontrmuseum.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Ontario Regiment</a> and the <a title=\"Queen's York Rangers\" href=\"http://qyrang.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Queen&#8217;s York Rangers</a>.  He has deployed to the <a title=\"United Nations Disengagement Observer Force\" href=\"http://www.un.org/en/peacekeeping/missions/undof/\" target=\"_blank\">Middle East</a>, the former <a title=\"UNITED NATIONS PROTECTION FORCE\" href=\"http://www.un.org/Depts/DPKO/Missions/unprof_b.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Yugoslavia</a> and most recently to <a title=\"Op Attention\" href=\"http://www.forces.gc.ca/en/operations-abroad-current/op-attention.page\" target=\"_blank\">Afghanistan</a>.</p>\n<p>His current appointment takes him out of his usual arcs and into the<a title=\"Canadian Infantry Association\" href=\"http://www.ducimus.com\" target=\"_blank\"> Infantry</a>, serving as the Regimental Sergeant-Major of the <a title=\"Royal Hamilton Light Infantry\" href=\"http://www.rhli.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Royal Hamilton Light Infantry</a>.  Grant is a good friend and a trusted advisor.  He has a deep commitment to caring for those soldiers that serve with him.</p>\n<p>His personal endeavour is called <a title=\"Toy Soldier Toronto\" href=\"http://toysoldiertoronto.com/onlinestore/\" target=\"_blank\">Toy Soldier Toronto</a>; check it out!</p>\n<p>Follow me on Twitter @MikeLacroix32</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-387-49\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-016-CWO-Grant-Lawson.mp3?_=49\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-016-CWO-Grant-Lawson.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-016-CWO-Grant-Lawson.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/grants-stuff-001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"grants stuff 001\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/grants-stuff-001-300x192.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"192\" /></a></p>\n<p>Young Grant Serving with the United Nations</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_0271-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-388\" alt=\"IMG_0271 (2)\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_0271-2-300x260.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_0271-2-300x260.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_0271-2-1024x889.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Grant on Op Attention in Afghanistan</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_20130713_122330.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-389\" alt=\"IMG_20130713_122330\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_20130713_122330-225x300.jpg\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_20130713_122330-225x300.jpg 225w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_20130713_122330-768x1024.jpg 768w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_20130713_122330.jpg 1938w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Grant arrives home and is greeted at Pearson International Airport</p>\n",
